main event: A civilian observer reported seeing an unidentified object near Poulsbo, Washington in January 1966.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 75-100 feet in diameter and dark in color.
The object remained stationary or moved slowly for about 15 minutes with no associated sound or vapor trail.
Multiple people in the area reported seeing the unusual object in the sky.
The observer was unsure of the exact number of objects seen and could not verify the accuracy of the witness accounts.
The Air Force concluded there was insufficient data to evaluate the report and requested the observer complete an additional questionnaire.
sighted object: A large, dark-colored object hovering or floating in the sky
